name: 19 Kids and Counting
overview: 19 Kids and Counting, rendered graphically as 19 Kids & Counting in its onscreen logo, is an American reality television show on TLC. The show is about the Duggar family, which consists of parents Jim Bob and Michelle Duggar and their 19 children—nine girls and ten boys, all of whose names begin with the letter "J". The series began on September 29, 2008. The twelfth season premiere was September 17, 2013.

episodes.name: Big Family Meets Big Apple
episodes.overview: The Duggars are heading to New York City to be featured on NBC's Today Show as part of Mother's Day. However, Michelle and Jim Bob Duggar have a big secret – Michelle is expecting baby #18, and the Duggars are trying to keep the news a secret until they can surprise the other 17 children on national television.

episodes.name: Duggars Do New York
episodes.overview: The Duggar's visit to New York City continues, as they visit Central Park and Times Square.

episodes.name: Josh Gets Engaged
episodes.overview: This episode features the Duggars rules about dating and courtship and includes a hidden camera view of oldest son Josh popping the big question to his fiancee Anna on her 20th birthday.

episodes.name: Duggar Dating Rules
episodes.overview: Josh brings Anna to Arkansas after the engagement in the last episode. The Duggars explain their beliefs about relationships with the opposite sex, where hand holding is a privilege, chaperones always accompany the couple and (in addition to their opposition to premarital sex) saving your first kiss for your wedding day is a must.

episodes.name: When Big Families Collide
episodes.overview: The Bates clan, a fellow mega-family from Tennessee (Gil, Kelly and their 16 children, with another on the way), decide to pay the Duggars a visit to their new Arkansas home. The episode centers around the logistical challenges of nearly 40 people in one house, as well as the similarities and differences between the two families.

episodes.name: Bates vs. Duggars Smackdown
episodes.overview: The Bates and Duggars compete in paintball and dare each other to jump out of an airplane.

episodes.name: Cheaper by the Duggars
episodes.overview: The Duggars explain their ways of thriftiness -- they do not use credit cards, only debit cards or cash; they purchase clothing from second hand stores, groceries from Aldi, grow their own vegetables, use firewood (from trees on their property) to heat their home and even have a recipe to make their own laundry detergent.

episodes.name: Trading Places, Duggar Style
episodes.overview: Each Duggar has his/her own chores (or jurisdictions, as they call them), which are somewhat gender-specific. However, Jim Bob decides that, on this day, the jurisdictions will switch and the boys will do the cooking, laundry and cleaning, while the girls learn the basics about car repairs.

episodes.name: Big Family Reunion
episodes.overview: The Duggars take a trip to Ohio for Michelle's family reunion. On the way, the family visits the Creation Museum in Petersburg, Kentucky where animatronic dinosaurs roam the earth with Adam and Eve. Prior to the trip Michelle goes in for an ultrasound, whereby the family learns that baby #18 is a girl.

episodes.name: Duggars Learn to Drive
episodes.overview: Jinger successfully passes her driving test. The Duggars also celebrate Michelle's birthday and discuss their upcoming book.

episodes.name: ...And Baby Makes 18!
episodes.overview: The family prepares for the arrival of the newest Duggar, Jordyn-Grace Makiya who will be delivered by Caesarean.

episodes.name: Once a Bride, Always a Duggar
I Left My Duggar in San Francisco
Duggars Say Yes to the Dress
Designing Duggars
episodes.overview: The Duggars and Wilsons help the Bates family finish their home renovation project while facing the challenges of trying to get everything done within a one-week deadline while 40 children are running around.

episodes.name: Duggars in the Sky
episodes.overview: The family meets the Nashville Predators hockey team. When the crew brings in a helicopter to film aerial shots, the kids get to see their house from a whole new height.

episodes.name: Special Duggar Delivery
episodes.overview: Baby No. 19, Josie Brooklyn Duggar, is welcomed into the family a little earlier than expected.

episodes.name: Josie Duggar's First Christmas
episodes.overview: The Duggars have already received an early Christmas present - the nineteenth Duggar, Josie. We'll track her progress and watch as the Duggars recount Christmases past.

episodes.name: Duggars Fly South
episodes.overview: Josh, Anna and Mackynzie take a trip to Florida to visit Anna's family for the first time since Mackynzie was born, and they make a special stop to reminisce about how they started their family.

episodes.name: Duggars Movin' Out
episodes.overview: With Josie still in the neonatal intensive care unit, the Duggar family make the decision to move to Little Rock, Arkansas to be closer to her. However, with with Jim Bob and Michelle busy with Josie, it's up to Grandma Duggar to set up the new home and watch over the little kids.

episodes.name: Duggars Dig In
episodes.overview: The Duggars are getting back into their routine after their move, but it isn't complete without a trip to the grocery store to buy for the family of 21. Also, Josie reaches an important milestone in her growth and Jim Bob and the oldest girls give blood.

episodes.name: Duggars in the Driver's Seat
episodes.overview: The Duggars participate in a radio fundraiser in an effort to give back to Arkansas Children's Hospital, which has been taking care of Josie.

episodes.name: Duggars and DJs
episodes.overview: The Duggars spend the day out and about in Little Rock, Arkansas, which includes a trip to the Discovery Museum. Also, when Michelle and Jim Bob get sick, Jana and Jill visit their littlest sister, Josie, and hold her for the very first time.

episodes.name: Josie Duggar Sisterhood
episodes.overview: Gil and Kelly Bates, along with their 17 children, travel to Little Rock, Arkansas to meet Josie for the first time. The families also visit a new church.

episodes.name: Josie Duggar Meets the Bates
episodes.overview: With Josie still in the hospital, the Duggars keep finding ways to welcome her to the family.

episodes.name: Josie Duggar's First Shoes
episodes.overview: The Duggars plan a day trip to Pinnacle Mountain complete with hiking, camouflage demonstration, and a picnic.

episodes.name: Duggar Mountain Way
episodes.overview: The Duggars visit Stone County Ironworks to learn about the art of blacksmithing. They also get to make their own ironworking project and listen to authentic bluegrass music.

episodes.name: Duggar Heavy Metal
episodes.overview: Jim Bob and some of the Duggar kids return to their home in Springdale, Arkansas to do some spring cleaning in preparation for Josie's homecoming. However, when she has a setback, the family must reunite in Little Rock once again.

episodes.name: Josie Comes Home
episodes.overview: Jim Bob and the children take a trip to the Little Rock Zoo. Also, Jim Bob and Michelle are able to witness another premature baby being treated while they are at the hospital to visit Josie.

episodes.name: Duggars at the Hospital
episodes.overview: Jim Bob and some of the Duggar kids return to their home in Springdale to do some spring cleaning in preparation for Josie's homecoming. However, when she has a setback, the family must reunite in Little Rock once again.

episodes.name: Duggars Go Wild
episodes.overview: Jim Bob and the children take a trip to the Little Rock Zoo. Also, Jim Bob and Michelle are able to witness another premature baby being treated while they are at the hospital to visit Josie.

episodes.name: Duggar Home Alone
episodes.overview: Jim Bob takes the children on a trip to Sandy, Texas to attend the ATI Home School Conference, while Michelle gets to spend some rare alone time at home and visits Josie at the hospital.

episodes.name: Duggar Dilemmas
episodes.overview: While doctors struggle to determine what's wrong with Josie's digestive system, Michelle and Jim Bob decide it's time for the other children to return to their home in Tontitown, Arkansas.

episodes.name: Digesting Duggars
episodes.overview: Doctors make a breakthrough with Josie when they determine the cause of her digestive problems. With the discovery comes relief when Michelle is finally able to bring Josie back home. Meanwhile, Jana and John David take off on their trip to Asia.

episodes.name: Duggars Go Hollywood
episodes.overview: The Duggars visit the set of the new film, Courageous. Meanwhile, Michelle continues to learn how to take care of Josie on her own back in Little Rock. This episodes features Alex Kendrick, Stephen Kendrick, and Harris Malcolm.

episodes.name: Dugger Want a Cracker
episodes.overview: It's no secret that the Duggar and Bates families find sanctuary in each other's company! But they take it a step further when the two families visit a parrot sanctuary in Pigeon Forge, Tennessee.

episodes.name: Duggars Chicken Out
episodes.overview: The Duggars trip back to their home in Tontitown, Arkansas is delayed when 12 of the kids come down with chicken pox.

episodes.name: Testy Duggars
episodes.overview: The Duggars adjust to life with a preemie, and Josie gets a new doctor, who tests her development and growth.

episodes.name: Duggars Do Dinner
episodes.overview: The Duggars are planning on having a dinner party and they invite two other large families to join in for a fun, and crowded, evening. And get an update on the three youngest Duggars - Jordyn, Josie, and first GrandDuggar, Mackynzie. It is also announced that Michelle is expecting number 20, but no, a crewman (Jon Boyle) and his wife are expecting first child.

episodes.name: Duggars Say Cheese
episodes.overview: The Duggars decide it's time to take new family photos now that Josie is home. But after the pictures are taken, Josie is off to a check-up where she gets another type of shot.

episodes.name: A Tale of Two Duggars
episodes.overview: Now that everyone is back in Tontitown, Jim Bob and Michelle, along with their kids, settle back into their daily routine. Also, Josh and Anna, along with Mackynzie, show us what their daily life is like for their smaller family.

episodes.name: Duggar Diagnosis
episodes.overview: It's a bittersweet time for the Duggars as Michelle finds out that her gallbladder, an initial cause of Josie's premature birth, may need more medical attention than originally thought.

episodes.name: Duggars and Sluggers
episodes.overview: Jim Bob takes the kids sight seeing in Louisville; Michelle prepares to leave Josie with a babysitters so she can reunite with the family.

episodes.name: Duggars Shoot for the Sky
episodes.overview: A new season begins as Jessa celebrates her 18th birthday with a trip to the shooting range and a skydiving adventure. Back at home, Michelle takes a pregnancy test to make sure she can go skydiving.

episodes.name: Duggars Rock the Vote
episodes.overview: John-David decides to follow in his dad's footsteps and run for political office. Also, Joseph gets braces and an update on Josh and Anna's second pregnancy.

episodes.name: Donating Duggars
episodes.overview: The family volunteers at the local fire department. Then, they travel to Oklahoma to help make supply parachutes for persecuted Colombians.

episodes.name: Duggars Rock & Record
episodes.overview: The Duggars return to Little Rock to help serve dinner at a fish fry. Also: Michelle records an audio book.

episodes.name: Duggars Act Out
episodes.overview: The Duggars attend a Passion play and are invited to become extras in the performance. Also: Jill gives Josie her first piano lesson.

episodes.name: Duggars All Aboard
episodes.overview: Joy-Anna turns 13, and the Duggars celebrate with a family train ride and an ice-cream party.

episodes.name: Duggars Explore Central America
episodes.overview: Jim Bob and 11 of the older kids embark on a volunteer mission to Central America. Back at home, Michelle keeps busy handling the seven little ones with limited help.

episodes.name: Duggars Make a Difference
episodes.overview: Jim Bob and the older kids continue their stay in Honduras, where they spend time with the locals, visit Mayan ruins and sample authentic Honduran cuisine.

episodes.name: Josie's First Birthday
episodes.overview: The Duggars celebrate Josie's first birthday.

episodes.name: Duggars Deliver
episodes.overview: Michelle spends time with the younger children and also tries to catch up on housework. Meanwhile, Anna learns firsthand the challenges of raising a 1-year-old.

episodes.name: Duggars in the Zone
episodes.overview: Josh and Anna are on a deadline to move their second used car lot, but due to zoning laws, they might not be able to make the move after all.

episodes.name: Duggars & Bates: 37 & Counting
episodes.overview: The Bates visit the Duggars. They are going to go to the George Washington Carver Monument, but a cold spreads through the two families which might ruin their plans.

episodes.name: Kids to the Rescue
episodes.overview: The Duggar kids stay back at home with lots of fun activities planned while Jim Bob and Michelle take a trip to El Salvador. But when Josie has a sudden health scare that sends her to the emergency room, her siblings must come to the rescue.

episodes.name: Duggars Focus on Family
episodes.overview: The Duggars share their secrets on how to run a large family while at a conference in Colorado. Later the family sneaks in some sightseeing, including a visit to the famed Garden of the Gods. And watch as the Duggars conquer their fear of heights.

episodes.name: Coffee and Caricatures
episodes.overview: Jessa and Jinger volunteer at a local coffee shop; Jackson and Johannah are drawing caricatures to collect funds for Josh and Anna's baby gift.

episodes.name: Pushups and Planting
episodes.overview: Jim Bob and Josh are in for a rude awakening when they meet their new trainer; one of Jill and Jana's clients goes into labor.

episodes.name: Duggars Snowed In
episodes.overview: When the worst snowstorm in Arkansas history hits the Duggars' hometown, the family is engulfed in a real winter wonderland. Watch as they weather the winter-weather with sledding, making snow cream and lending a hand to their neighbors in need.

episodes.name: Duggar Boys Day Out
episodes.overview: Jackson gets to hang out with the older Duggar boys as they demolish and renovate the new car lot.

episodes.name: Waiting...
episodes.overview: Michelle takes Josie for a check-up; Jessa shows discipline to get the younger Duggars down for a nap.

episodes.name: Dinner for Forty
episodes.overview: Trainer Steve's family, along with Pastor Howard and his family come by for big dinner.

episodes.name: Duggars Respond & Rescue
episodes.overview: The Duggars celebrate Grandma's 70th birthday; the Duggars rush to help the search and rescue efforts in Joplin.

episodes.name: Manhattan Duggars
episodes.overview: The Duggars head to NYC to kick off their book tour; Jim Bob, Michelle and all 19 kids try to navigate the NYC subway system.

episodes.name: Baby Gender Reveal and the Final Weigh In
episodes.overview: Josh and Anna are caught off guard when the entire family visits Restoration Church where Pastor Howard reveals some baby secret news.

episodes.name: Duggar Grandson on Board
episodes.overview: The first Duggar grandson is having a full day of firsts: baby Michael has his very first checkup—complete with his very first shot, meets his cousin Amy for the very first time, and is a guest at his very first Duggar birthday party.

episodes.name: Duggars Over the Edge
episodes.overview: The family visits one of the largest waterfalls in North America—Niagara Falls. The Duggars (who are prone to motion sickness) spend the day riding the Maid of the Mist, challenging the Cave of the Winds, and checking out the Jet Boat and Fort Niagara.

episodes.name: Duggar Campout
episodes.overview: The Duggars are roughing it—sort of. Jim Bob sets up a tent for an at-home campout, complete with s'mores and scary stories. Despite a soaring daytime temperature of 105 degrees, the family proceeded with the campout.

episodes.name: Schoolhouse Duggars
episodes.overview: Michelle demonstrates her homeschooling skills as the family prepares for their annual ATI Conference in Big Sandy, Texas. Then, the Duggar kids put what they have learned to practice visiting a Spanish tutor and ordering in Spanish at a restaurant.

episodes.name: Duggar In Danger
episodes.overview: The Duggars are in Atlanta for a little work and a lot of play. After attending a speaking engagement, it's time for some fun in the water, which includes jet skiing, tubing and wake boarding. But happiness turns to worry when Jason has a painful and terrifying accident.

episodes.name: Duggars Under the Sea
episodes.overview: The Duggars are under water—in an aquarium that is. The Duggars continue their visit in Atlanta, Georgia with their first ever trip to an aquarium. Later, the family meets professional surfer and shark attack survivor Bethany Hamilton.

episodes.name: 38 Kids & Counting!
episodes.overview: It's a full house when the Duggars once again visit their friends, the Bates. The two families join their 38 combined kids for some fellowship and fun. In addition, the oldest Bates son, Zach, makes a very special request to his girlfriend Sarah to begin a courtship.

episodes.name: Daddy Duggar's Birthday
episodes.overview: It's Jim Bob's birthday, but before he can celebrate, he must visit the allergist and get several rounds of allergy injections.

episodes.name: Do Good Duggars
episodes.overview: The Duggars go to Alabama to help Habitat for Humanity rebuild homes destroyed by tornadoes.

episodes.name: Duggars: All You Wanted to Know
episodes.overview: The Duggars answer questions taken directly from the viewers. This is followed by an announcement that they were expecting a 20th child.

episodes.name: Jill's Secret
episodes.overview: The Duggars plants trees and visit a corn maze. Michelle speaks at a women's meeting; the older girls go with her, leaving Jim Bob to take care of the little ones alone. Later, Michelle and Jim Bob go in for a pregnancy check up.

episodes.name: Josh & Anna Check In
episodes.overview: Mackynzie gets her first haircut. Josh and Anna provide updates on their car lot and their son Michael.

episodes.name: 40 Kids, Oh My!
episodes.overview: A family as big as the Duggars, the Vanderhoffs, comes to visit. Jim Bob stays home and plays host while Michelle visits her friend of 39 years. Michelle also does a speaking engagement at a Moms' meeting.

episodes.name: Music with the Duggars
episodes.overview: The Duggars go to Branson, Missouri for a speaking engagement and musical performance, where Amy performs live onstage.

episodes.name: The Duggar Twist
episodes.overview: The Duggars visit a pretzel shop and helps raise money for Alex's Lemonade Stand Foundation, an organization that is aimed at fighting childhood cancer.

episodes.name: Duggars in Space
episodes.overview: The Duggars go to Space Camp. The family tests their strengths and skills by doing astronaut training activities such as a multi-axis trainer and flight simulator.

episodes.name: Swerve and Serve
episodes.overview: The Duggars meet up with some old friends and volunteer at a fish fry. Joy Anna celebrates her 14th birthday with her first driving lesson from Michelle.

episodes.name: Boys Day Out
episodes.overview: Jim Bob takes his sons to Fort Rock Family Camp for a father/son campout. Before the boys leave, Joy Anna has a special treat for them.

episodes.name: A Duggar Loss
episodes.overview: Michelle and Jim Bob visit the obstetrician for another routine ultrasound checkup of their baby, only to receive devastating news that there had been a miscarriage.

episodes.name: All You Can Eat
episodes.overview: A stroll down memory lane and see just how much the little ones have grown. A peek at the Duggars' enormous pantry and all the food it takes to feed a family of 21.

episodes.name: Puppies, Properties & Patients
episodes.overview: The Duggars pet sit for a pair of puppies and Michelle must manage both the children and the pets. Later, the family renovates a new property.

episodes.name: Smile and Say Duggars
episodes.overview: The family returns to Joplin, Mo. for a Mother's Day Fundraiser for the victims of the tornado in 2011; it's picture day for the Duggars.

episodes.name: Duggars Dinner Party
episodes.overview: The Duggars welcome the Pope family for dinner whose son was in the NICU with Josie; it is a family affair when they help Josh move vehicles from one used car lot to another.

episodes.name: Busy Duggars
episodes.overview: Johannah turns 6 and learns to do things the big girl way; Jim Bob takes the family fishing and hiking; the older girls and cousin Amy let Grandma know how much she means to them.

episodes.name: Dinner for Forty
episodes.overview: Trainer Steve's family, along with Pastor Howard and his family come by for big dinner.

episodes.name: The Duggar Brides
episodes.overview: The family heads to Nashville, Tenn., to help out with a charity event called Laundry Love; a visit to the Grand Ole Opry.

episodes.name: Waiting...
episodes.overview: Cameras capture life in the Duggar family, with 19 children so far.

episodes.name: Baby Steps
episodes.overview: Josh and Anna have added a new member to their family, a kitten; little Michael is about to take his first steps.

episodes.name: Kittens and Konstruction
episodes.overview: The Duggars are up to their knees in kittens; Michelle must teach the little ones how to take care of their newest additions.

episodes.name: First Grandson Turns 1
episodes.overview: The first Duggar Grandson Michael turns 1; Anna decides to make a cake for her birthday boy.

episodes.name: Thrill Seeking Duggars
episodes.overview: The Duggars head to Branson, Mo. to ride roller coasters; Vanderhoffs for dinner; Jill turns 21.

episodes.name: Fencing & Fireworks
episodes.overview: The Duggars are lighting up the sky after the family purchases fireworks for the 4th of July. Then, Jim Bob takes some of the family to their first fencing lesson. And finally, the older girls start preparing for Michelle's birthday celebration.

episodes.name: Michelle's Birthday Makeover
episodes.overview: Michelle Duggar is getting a birthday of a lifetime as the older Duggar girls, Amy and Anna prepare a day of surprises for her birthday but perhaps the biggest surprise may be from Jim Bob himself. Michelle has a little surprise for the family of her own.

episodes.name: Baby on the Way
episodes.overview: After the Duggars return home from Asia, Anna invites the family over to tell them the news that she and Josh are expecting baby number three. Jana and Jill are studying to be midwives and spend an afternoon seeing patients, alongside a licensed midwife.

episodes.name: Duggar Weight Loss Challenge
episodes.overview: Jim Bob and Josh start a 90-day weight-loss competition. Jason and his brothers build a greenhouse.

episodes.name: Things Are Changing
episodes.overview: Priscilla (Anna's sister, who is also pregnant with her first baby) and her husband, David, visit, which prompts Josh and Anna to seek a house with more space. Jim Bob and Josh receive the results from their medical exams, which are surprising.

episodes.name: Pushups and Planting
episodes.overview: Jim Bob and Josh are surprised when they meet their new trainer, while Jana and Jill have a client who goes into labor.

episodes.name: Duggars Take Flight
episodes.overview: John-David is close to getting his pilot's license, Joseph leaves home for the first time, to go to train with an emergency rescue team. Jim-Bob and Josh check on with, Steve, on their weight loss.

episodes.name: Love and Marriage
episodes.overview: Jim Bob and Michelle talk about their marriage, the ups and downs of it all, before going to a marriage retreat, to help make their marriage stronger.

episodes.name: Dinner for Forty
episodes.overview: Former NFL player Steve Conley and Pastor Howard, come to the Duggars' home for dinner, with their families.

episodes.name: A Surgery and a Secret
episodes.overview: Jim Bob & Josh feel the pain from their workouts. Josh takes Anna for an ultrasound to find out the sex of their baby. Jordyn has to have her tonsils taken out.

episodes.name: Decisions & Deliveries
episodes.overview: Josh is presented with a job opportunity 1,200 miles away, will he take it? Jana and Jill's client goes into labor and the family attends Joseph's boot camp graduation.

episodes.name: Duggars Get Physical
episodes.overview: After several weeks of training, trainer Steve pushes Jim Bob and Josh to their max, all leading up to the final weigh in. Then they head down to Florida, to visit Anna's family and meet the latest family addition, her newborn nephew, Paul.

episodes.name: Baby Gender Reveal & the Final Weigh In
episodes.overview: The Duggars surprise Josh and Anna, by visiting them at Pastor Howard's church, where he reveals the sex of their baby. Jim Bob and Josh have their last weigh-in to see who won the weight-loss challenge. Josh makes a final decision on whether or not to take the job offer in, Washington, D.C.

episodes.name: Big Changes
episodes.overview: It's a time of exciting and emotional changes for the Duggars as Josh & Anna move to Washington, DC. But before the goodbyes, the couple still has one important thing to do...

episodes.name: An Emotional Goodbye
episodes.overview: The Duggars knew that eventually one of their 19 children would move away and that bittersweet milestone has arrived: it's time for the Duggar family to say goodbye to Josh & Anna.

episodes.name: Farm Fresh Duggars
episodes.overview: Are the Duggars ready to take on raising more than just 19 kids? Jim Bob thinks they're ready to raise cows, chickens and pigs too! The Duggar family spends the day on a working farm to see what it would be like if they had one in their own backyard.

episodes.name: Flea Market Finale
episodes.overview: The family gears up for a flea market to benefit the Arkansas Children's Hospital; a long to-do list and an ambitious goal.
